description:
Open for recipe 👇

Want a jam recipe that keeps the irresistible flavor of your fresh fruit? Chia jam requires no cooking and no white sugar to dull the taste of your fruit, so the sun-ripened flavor of your berries is preserved. Make this chia jam with fresh blackberries or substitute other fresh fruit in season. Chia jam can be stored up to a week in the fridge or up to three months in the freezer.

Blackberry Chia Jam
2 tbsp ground chia seeds
3 tbsp coconut water
1 cup blackberries
1/2 cup apple sauce
1 tbsp lemon juice 
1 tbsp coconut nectar 

Vegan, gluten free, soy free, dairy free
